process_name: Make a Gas Mask - Making an Air Filter for your Mask
step_1: Attach a homemade air filtration system to your mask to protect from some gases
step_2: Cut off the top of a 1-liter bottle
step_3: Fill the bottom of the bottle with 3–4 inches (7
step_4: 6–10 cm) of activated charcoal
step_5: Cut the bottom off another 1-liter bottle
step_6: Fill the top of the bottle with 3-4 inches of pillow stuffing
step_7: Poke 6-7 holes in the charcoal end of your filter when you’re ready to use it
step_8: Use a rubber hose to connect the bottom of your air mask to your filter
step_9: Replace your activated charcoal with each use

process_name: Tell If Someone Is in Your Closet
step_1: Say something funny
step_2: Listen for any rustling or breathing from the closet
step_3: Look for any signs that your closet has been opened or tampered with, generally a badly closed door or something moved out of the way
step_4: Turn on the light (or use a flashlight) to peer inside the closet before opening it if your closet has a slit in it
step_5: If you have a temperature gun and your closet has cracks, fire that inside and look for temperature spikes
step_6: Lock your closet somehow
step_7: Bang on the closet door loudly
step_8: Ask "Is anyone inside of my closet?" Slowly open the closet door, having a good grip on the handle and using your foot to prevent the door from opening far
step_9: Repeat step 7 until the door is fully open

process_name: Service an Air Conditioner - Clean the Air Conditioner
step_1: Make sure the unit is turned off either at the on/off switch and unplugging it or by shutting off the circuit breaker
step_2: Check the small copper pipe connecting the unit to the house
step_3: Rake any leaves and debris away from the unit before you start to service an air conditioner
step_4: Take the cover off the unit, and locate the air conditioner coils (they look like a car radiator)
step_5: Use a soft brush to brush any dirt and debris off the outside cover
step_6: Cover the motor and wiring with a plastic sheet
step_7: Hose down the fins, coils and inside of the unit
step_8: Check your owner's manual
step_9: Replace the unit cover, and turn it on to make sure it runs properly

process_name: Fix a Bicep Tear - Resuming Physical Activity
step_1: Resume activities slowly and only after the pain subsides
step_2: Begin with pendulum exercises

step_5: Do 10 supination and pronation stretches
step_6: Do 10 internal and external rotations

step_8: Use resistance bands after at least a week of pain-free stretching
step_9: Do 2 sets of 8 to 12 biceps curls

process_name: Brown a Roast for Cooking in a Crockpot
step_1: Rinse the roast with cold water
step_2: Place the meat on a cutting board
step_3: Pat it dry with paper towels, pressing to absorb as much water as possible
step_4: Trim any excess fat off the meat
step_5: Cut the roast into smaller pieces if it is too large to fit into your crockpot
step_6: Heat 2 tablespoons (30 mm) of cooking oil in a large Dutch oven on medium high heat
step_7: Sprinkle and rub salt and pepper all over the meat
step_8: Brown the meat in the hot oil for several minutes on each side
step_9: Remove the seared meat and place it in the crockpot you’ll use to roast it

process_name: Field Dress a Deer - Removing the Entrails
step_1: Position the deer with its head facing uphill
step_2: Slice into the belly just deep enough to get through the skin
step_3: Slice the skin all the way up to the neck and down to the anus
step_4: Make an incision into the middle of the belly muscle and insert 2 fingers into the hole
step_5: Insert the blade facing up between the 2 fingers you inserted
step_6: Cut all the way up the deer’s midline without piercing the entrails
step_7: Remove the sex organs if they’re in the way (when applicable)
step_8: Cut a hole around the anus, then tie it off from the inside to prevent spilling
step_9: Roll the deer on its side and carefully pull out the entrails with your hands

process_name: Add Colorful Emoticons, Icons and Smiley Faces in Outlook
step_1: Go to "New" button and create a new message (email)
step_2: Come to the main message section and through the "Picture" button present on the top Menu bar, insert an image or logo
step_3: After Insertion of a particular image, select it to use in further procedure
step_4: Now, go to the "AutoCorrect" option by following this path: After clicking on "AutoCorrect" button, other pop-up window will appear on screen which brings you directly to setting page of "AutoCorrect" option
step_5: Write the character on which you want conversion of image or emoticons in the "Replace" field
step_6: You have to verify that by "With" option
step_7: Add it by clicking on the "Add" button
step_8: To confirm about adding of that particular image or logo, see the list given below under "With" option
step_9: Click on the "OK" button and now you can use the pictures or images in your email by just typing that particular character which you have defined for them
